<a href="javascript:card_browser(133)">Band of the Eye</a>x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> light side<br>
basically you bid high around 3 or 4 and go first. drop the pony pull aragorn out. get out his goodies like saga of elendil, ranger sword, last allaiance of elves and men, but most importantly get out his bow. <br>
Then get out your allies elrond and the dwarfs along with galadriel and her elevs. With a shoulder to shoulder you are creating an engine where you are healing arwen who in turns heals aragorn. Your dwarfs are also healing legolas.<br>
example--- legolas with gilgalad tale and aragorn who has his bow and the saga on are exhausted, arwen has no wounds. your opponent drops a keyward with his troll. During maneuver phase pay one to exert grimir to heal legolas(courtesy of shoulder to shoulder). pay another one to exert thrarin to heal legolas. pay another one and exert grimir to heal legolas. Now legolas is all healed. Exert arwen twice to the choice to heal aragorn twice. Now pay one exert elrond to heal grimir. pay one exert grimir to heal arwen.pay one to exert galadriel to heal grimir. pay one exert grimir and heal arwen. exert arwen twice more and heal aragorn. pay one and exert rumil to heal grimir. pay one exert grimir to heal arwen and so far. Now in archery phase you can shoot down both the keyward and the troll.<br>
Boromir and sam are in there to make sure th ebalrog doesnt kill anyone apart of the shoulder to shoulder engine. Thats their whole purpose is to be fodder just in case they get by your archers.<br>
use thror&#39;s map so you can have your site 7 played instead of annoying anduin confluence(skip archery phase, or the discard all allies one.<br>
usually you will be making one move a turn. because at the beging of your turn all your allies heal due to elronds and galadriels power.<br>
<br>
weakness----spies of saurman and goblins that make you discard elven allies/dwarfs. could be dangerous.<br>
<br>
shadow<br>
basically you want to get the pain going early by dropping a couple utwe&#39;s on your opponet. The orc bowmen follow up with some of their on. And hate away exhausted companions. Use thin and strecthed to get the burdens high and then surprise your opponent with enduring evil which should guarantee you an overwhelmed companion. <br>
weakness--any type of twilight choke deck can clog up the shadow side. so use gwemgil to get rid of a few extra cards if this is the case. Use the arv  for when you are planning on double moving, like froom 7-8 or 8-9. modify this deck how you want. use different shadow sides. But i have found succes with saurons. I just won a tournament 5-0. check out my tournament report clarks summit.also dont forget aragorn heals arwen at the start of every turn:)<br>
<br>
if you have any questions just ask and i can give you more detail. thanks. steve </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=22821"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=22821" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
